rictly, a real solution to the problem.I keep falling back to what somebody once called "pitman's two-bit rule"of language design -- it goes something like: if you have two bits ofinfo to represent, use at least two bits to do the representation. Sinceinteractiveness of the input argument and need for query are potentiallyorthogonal, you can't get away with passing only one argument and usingit for both purposes without running into trouble some of the time. Amore robust solution would add a :DETAILED or :VERBOSE option toDESCRIBE, which could be T, NIL, or :ASK.*start*01160 00024 USaReturn-Path: <@multimax.ARPA:pierson%mist@multimax.ARPA>Received: from multimax.ARPA ([192.5.63.14]) by Xerox.COM ; 01 NOV 88 07:08:47 PSTReceived:  by multimax.ARPA (5.51/25-eef)	id AA26493; Tue, 1 Nov 88 10:06:43 ESTReceived: from localhost by mist.UUCP (3.2/4.7)	id AA29890; Tue, 1 Nov 88 10:10:39 ESTMessage-Id: <8811011510.AA29890@mist.UUCP>To: masinter.pa%Xerox.COM@MULTIMAX.ENCORE.COMCc: Moon%STONY-BROOK.SCRC.Symbolics.COM@MULTIMAX.ENCORE.COMSubject: Re: Issue: DESCRIBE-INTERACTIVE (Version 3) In-Reply-To: Your message of 31 Oct 88 11:19:00 -0800.             <881031-112022-6051@Xerox> Date: Tue, 01 Nov 88 10:10:36 ESTFrom: Dan L. Pierson <pierson%mist@MULTIMAX.ENCORE.COM>This is the sort of response I wanted, I'll be happy to write up a newversion with additional discussion including Moon's complaints andexplicit note that this is an incompatible change.  If either of youwant, I'll also add a second proposal based on the "interactiveness"of the stream (I don't object to such a proposal in principal; I justhate to see a multi-proposal go out to the mail ballot unless it'sabsolutely necessary.)*start*01792 00024 US Date: 31 Oct 88 11:19 PSTFrom: masinter.paSubject: Re: Issue: DESCRIBE-INTERACTIVE (Version 3) In-reply-to: Dan L. Pierson <pierson%mist@MULTIMAX.ENCORE.COM>'s message of Mon, 31 Oct 88 13:21:15 ESTTo: Dan L. Pierson <pierson%mist@M